Preconditions:
The input grid must be a 2D array of integers.
The grid must contain at least two islands.
Each island in the grid must be represented by the value Each water area in the grid must be represented by the value 
Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the smallest number of 0's that need to be flipped to connect the two islands.
The grid should remain unchanged after the method is executed.